## 4.5 Linked Allocation — Disk Map

```mermaid
graph LR
    MFD3["MFD entry fileA start=3 next=NULL"] --> B3["Block 3 data next=47"]
    B3 --> B47["Block 47 data next=12"]
    B47 --> B12["Block 12 data next=88"]
    B12 --> B88["Block 88 data next=NULL"]
    style MFD3 fill:#FFF3B0,stroke:#B7950B,color:#000
    style B3 fill:#D5F5E3,stroke:#239B56,color:#000
    style B47 fill:#D5F5E3,stroke:#239B56,color:#000
    style B12 fill:#D5F5E3,stroke:#239B56,color:#000
    style B88 fill:#D5F5E3,stroke:#239B56,color:#000
```

**Interpretation:** File `fileA` occupies blocks `3 → 47 → 12 → 88` — scattered across disk. The MFD only stores the head pointer (block 3); each block carries a `next` pointer to the following block. To read the 3rd block of the file, the OS follows 2 pointers (3 → 47 → 12).

